snippet.title: How To Integrate ML NET with a Chat Bot
snippet.description:
Announcing .NET Core 3.0: https://aka.ms/dotnetcore3 

Are a .NET developer interested in Machine Learning? Using ML.NET and Visual Studio you can create the best ML model for your data. It won't take much time. No ML experience needed! Then you can use the model in all kinds of applications including Azure Web App Bot.

snippet.title: Bot Framework V4 BotBuilder .NET Core - #6 - Sentiment analysis Middleware with ML.NET
snippet.description:
In this video I show you how to add sentiment analysis Middleware which will detect the sentiment of each message using a custom ML.NET model.  

Code - https://github.com/jamesemann/bot-framework-v4-intro-dotnet-core

The ML.NET code in this example is based on https://docs.microsoft.com/en-gb/dotnet/machine-learning/tutorials/sentiment-analysis

IMDB large movie review dataset - http://ai.stanford.edu/~amaas/data/sentiment/

snippet.title: Sentiment Analysis with .NET for Apache Spark + ML.NET: Part 1 | .NET for Apache Spark 101 [5 of 8]
snippet.description:
Big data and machine learning are a powerful combination for data processing and analysis. Learn how to leverage ML.NET (through the easy-to-use Model Builder UI) in combination with .NET for Apache Spark to perform sentiment analysis on a set of online reviews.

snippet.title: Saving and Loading Binary Data in ML.NET
snippet.description:
Binary data can give a performance boost when loading. This video shows how to save and load binary data in your ML.NET applications to build models against.

Code - https://github.com/jwood803/MLNetExamples/blob/master/MLNetExamples/BinaryData/Program.cs
